**Abstract:**
Working notes dated November 4, 1992, examining the concept of philosophy used by medieval thinkers, particularly through analysis of the Gilson-Van Steenberghen debate on "Christian philosophy." The document explores the distinction between philosophy as Weltanschauung and philosophy as scientific discipline, critiques Van Steenberghen's position on the separation of theological and philosophical domains, and argues that his distinction creates unresolvable contradictions.

**AI Recommendation:** Important methodological notes on Christian philosophy debate; documents author's critical engagement with Van Steenberghen.

